<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="391" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d391">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">891.77/7–2444</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ford</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 1039</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-24">July 24,
                                    1944</date>.<lb/>[Received August 7.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to the
                                Department’s telegram No. 409 of July 6, 1944 instructing the
                                Legation to advise the authorities concerned that the United States
                                Government feels it unnecessary to join in the proposed
                                Irano-American-Soviet-British agreement on financial
                                responsibilities for the war-time operation of the Iranian State
                                Railways. The British Embassy was informed of this decision by
                                letter dated July 12, a copy of which was sent to the Soviet
                                Embassy. To date, I have had no reply nor comment from either
                                Embassy.</p>
                            <p>Since the Legation had never discussed the question with the Iranian
                                authorities, no notification of the Department’s decision has been
                                made to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.</p>
                            <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Ford</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>